67
00:05:04,860 --> 00:05:07,400
I want to eat Italian food.

68
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,220
Look at him!

69
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:13,080
What kind of outfit is that?

70
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:15,080
Why is he all covered up?

71
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:18,520
Exactly. I guess he's scared to die of pneumonia.

72
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:22,680
Look at Dol.

73
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,860
The way he dresses is so strange.

74
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,340
Do you want an umbrella?

75
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,620
Do you want one?

76
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,520
Oh, you already have it. What about you?

77
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:49,480
I already have mine.

78
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,120
But my umbrellas are prettier. Look at the color.

79
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,080
No, thank you.

80
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:54,940
Do you want a raincoat?

81
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:55,620
No, thanks.

82
00:05:58,460 --> 00:06:00,380
Bro, do you want a raincoat? I have umbrellas too.

83
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:02,140
You don't want one?

84
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:04,200
You want to buy?

85
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,540
Choose whichever color you like. I have this one as well.

86
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:08,880
How about the green one? It suits you.

87
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:10,780
You want the pink one?

88
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,280
Who is that guy?

89
00:06:58,340 --> 00:06:59,600
I don't know too.

90
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,480
Heng!

91
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:03,500
Bro!

92
00:07:04,140 --> 00:07:05,220
I'm in trouble now!

93
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:08,940
I met my soulmate.

94
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:12,960
Huh? What do you mean?

95
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:17,320
I got wet in the rain, and then I saw him in full color.

96
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:21,760
Aren't you soulmate blind?

97
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,440
Maybe...

98
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,760
Your boyfriend lied to you.

99
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,880
Ex-boyfriend!

100
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:34,280
Oh, right, ex-boyfriend.

101
00:07:36,220 --> 00:07:39,560
Au definitely lied to you.

102
00:07:39,700 --> 00:07:43,100
He said you're his soulmate, so you wouldn't dare to break up with him.

103
00:07:44,340 --> 00:07:45,520
We've already broken up.

104
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:48,140
You keep saying that.

105
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:51,000
How many times have you broken up already? You'll get back with him again.

106
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:53,640
This time, we really broke up for good.

107
00:07:55,340 --> 00:07:56,800
I hope it's true.

108
00:07:57,440 --> 00:08:00,920
But you should stop acting like a bank that lends money first.

109
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:03,740
How much did he waste on football betting?

110
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,360
I know.

111
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:06,760
I'm so done with him.

112
00:08:08,260 --> 00:08:09,440
But are you sure?

113
00:08:10,180 --> 00:08:11,680
That you actually met your soulmate.

114
00:08:12,020 --> 00:08:13,320
I'm sure!

115
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,060
He's a man.

116
00:08:16,260 --> 00:08:17,960
He was waiting for the van to go home.

117
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,900
He's handsome too!

118
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:20,880
Wait a minute.

119
00:08:21,740 --> 00:08:23,640
So that means he's working in this area.

120
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,480
You're right!

121
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,620
I know what to do.

122
00:08:27,860 --> 00:08:28,820
I have to prove it.

123
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:34,260
Tomorrow, I'll go to the bus stop and wait for him, and I'll ask him,

124
00:08:34,820 --> 00:08:36,500
'Do you see me in color?'

125
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:37,940
I can see you in color!

126
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,800
What do you think?

127
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:44,640
Or maybe there's something wrong with my body.

128
00:08:45,340 --> 00:08:47,420
Am I going to die? Oh my God!

129
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:52,240
You're talking nonsense.

130
00:08:52,980 --> 00:08:53,700
Come on!

131
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:57,480
I think this plan will work.

132
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:02,200
I'm going now.

133
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:04,900
Hey! Pay for your cat food first.

134
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:08,280
Add it to my bill. I'll come back to pay later.

135
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,020
I knew it.

136
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:16,960
Eh?

137
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:20,600
Who gave you the food?

138
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:25,260
It's okay.

139
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:28,120
I'll give you an umbrella instead.

140
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,400
There you go.

141
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:35,380
It's going to rain for 30 days.

142
00:09:35,740 --> 00:09:38,280
Use this umbrella so you won't get wet.

143
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,480
Umbrellas!

144
00:10:12,340 --> 00:10:13,160
Mister!

145
00:10:14,620 --> 00:10:16,440
You're feeding the Midnight gang?

146
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,540
What are you talking about?

147
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:23,060
You don't have to raise your voice.

148
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,460
What's your name?

149
00:10:24,860 --> 00:10:25,900
Is your office in this area?

150
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,360
Really?

151
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,680
Let's get straight to business.

152
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:35,840
Can you please confirm the answer for me?

153
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:38,240
I see you in color. Do you see me in color as well?

154
00:10:38,460 --> 00:10:39,320
If it's a yes,

155
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,580
then we're soulmates.

156
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,540
It doesn't matter.

157
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:48,800
Yes, it is! We're soulmates!

158
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,360
How about this?

159
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:53,640
Can I get to know you more? Please.

160
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,340
Let's be on our own paths.

161
00:10:56,380 --> 00:10:57,280
Why?

162
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:58,720
Eh?

163
00:10:59,120 --> 00:10:59,880
Mister!

164
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:01,500
Mister!

165
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:19,580
Why is he playing hard to get?

166
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:47,080
Au: Can we go back to how things used to be?

167
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:53,720
Really?

168
00:11:54,420 --> 00:11:55,060
Yes.

169
00:11:56,420 --> 00:11:58,040
I can see you in color.

170
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:04,160
You've never heard of 'soulmate blind'?

171
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:08,100
1% of people in this world cannot see their soulmate.

172
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:13,080
I guess you're one of them.

173
00:12:15,660 --> 00:12:17,240
This sucks.

174
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:19,940
It's already hard to find your own soulmate.

175
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:23,240
And I'm also in that 1% of people.

176
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:28,360
It's okay.

177
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:31,820
Just know that we're soulmates. That's enough.

178
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:39,480
Delete.

179
00:12:54,140 --> 00:12:55,120
Here you go.

180
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,520
So, is there any update?

181
00:12:58,700 --> 00:13:00,040
I wish! I came back empty-handed.

182
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:02,820
He got angry when I started talking about soulmates.

183
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,940
Did you annoy him?

184
00:13:05,940 --> 00:13:08,560
Me? Annoyed him? Are you mad?

185
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:11,720
Also, the way he dressed was completely covered up.

186
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:13,520
He was wearing a raincoat and boots.

187
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,480
Why is he so afraid of the rain? What a weirdo.

188
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:18,160
Whoa, look at you!

189
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,960
It's not like you're not weird.

190
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:25,480
I'm weird? I'm completely normal and handsome.

191
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:27,220
I won't back down.

192
00:13:28,420 --> 00:13:29,800
I won't give up.

193
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:32,180
I will keep approaching him.

194
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:33,800
Whatever.

195
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,580
Bro, there's an order. See you later.

196
00:13:38,780 --> 00:13:40,200
Alright, see you.

197
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:42,140
Count the money too. Make sure it's correct

198
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:53,380
Hello.

199
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:54,860
Your food is here.

200
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:57,520
I'm waiting in front of the building.

201
00:13:58,240 --> 00:13:59,360
Sure.

202
00:14:00,140 --> 00:14:01,040
Okay.

203
00:14:24,580 --> 00:14:25,960
I'm here to pick up my food.

204
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,680
Oh, here you go.

205
00:14:31,820 --> 00:14:34,080
And you're... Dol, right?

206
00:14:35,140 --> 00:14:36,280
Are you working here?

207
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:37,260
Thank you.

208
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:43,200
I always deliver food here. How come I’ve never seen you before?

209
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:49,600
Also, if you don't want to get wet from the rain, I can come to pick you up.

210
00:14:49,940 --> 00:14:51,580
Mister! It's free for you!

211
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:56,660
Mister!

212
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:00,620
Mister!

213
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:05,300
You want to go to the bus stop, right? I'll take you there.

214
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:07,620
It's okay.

215
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,400
Come on. We know each other now. No need to worry!

216
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:11,380
Please.

217
00:15:11,680 --> 00:15:12,480
It's okay.

218
00:15:13,780 --> 00:15:17,880
Please. It's free. I won't add extra charges just for you.

219
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:19,560
No, thank you.

220
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:23,320
Please, let me give you a ride.

221
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:25,500
I told you no.

222
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:28,420
Mister!

223
00:15:30,260 --> 00:15:31,540
Are you alright?

224
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:33,080
I'm fine.

225
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:35,180
Let me help you.

226
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:47,240
You can hardly walk, and you still say you're fine?

227
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:48,820
Let me help you.

228
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,260
I'm fine, seriously.

229
00:15:51,260 --> 00:15:53,200
Will you let me buy that word from you so you won't say it again?

230
00:15:54,820 --> 00:15:56,200
You're so stubborn.

231
00:15:56,980 --> 00:15:58,600
I'll take you to get your wound treated.

232
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:00,480
Walk slowly.

233
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,280
May I?

234
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:13,300
Are you okay?

235
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:19,740
Let's go. I can assure you of your safety.

236
00:16:23,020 --> 00:16:24,080
Trust me.

237
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:29,880
Let me see.

238
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:34,900
I told you I would drop you off. You're so stubborn.

239
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,440
You see? You were grazed by the motorcycle.

240
00:16:38,860 --> 00:16:40,240
It's not that serious.

241
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:41,400
It is.

242
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:46,600
You shouldn't keep saying that everything is fine when you're hurt.

243
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:50,220
If it hurts, then just say so. Do you understand?

244
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:54,800
Let me put it on for you.

245
00:16:56,940 --> 00:16:57,860
It will hurt a bit.

246
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:07,400
And don't forget to put the medicine on your ankle too.

247
00:17:08,060 --> 00:17:09,820
It will definitely throb tomorrow.

248
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:16,240
Here. Take it.

249
00:17:22,180 --> 00:17:23,340
- Thank you.
- What?

250
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:27,660
Thank you.

251
00:17:27,660 --> 00:17:28,800
Your welcome.

252
00:17:30,060 --> 00:17:31,140
It's nothing.

253
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:36,580
By the way, can I ask you something?

254
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:41,580
When I see you, you always dress so covered up.

255
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,000
Don't you feel hot?

256
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,440
It's about to rain.

257
00:17:46,860 --> 00:17:48,100
So I have to wear a raincoat.

258
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:49,940
I understand.

259
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:52,520
But I guess you're really scared of the rain, aren't you?

260
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:57,520
Yeah.

261
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:00,280
But rain...

262
00:18:02,220 --> 00:18:03,980
It makes us see each other in color.

263
00:18:06,180 --> 00:18:07,780
Are you going to talk about this same topic again?

264
00:18:13,860 --> 00:18:15,740
But we're actually soulmates, aren't we?

265
00:18:19,260 --> 00:18:20,800
You can see me in color.

266
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:24,320
I can see you in color too.

267
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:25,720
Is this real?

268
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:38,700
Yes.

269
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:41,500
I can see you in color.

270
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:50,080
- So that means--
- I don't believe in such things.

271
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:50,820
Oh.

272
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:56,400
There're so many people who love each other even though they're not soulmates.

273
00:18:57,180 --> 00:18:58,740
And their life as a couple can be good.

274
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,340
There are some couples...

275
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:04,920
who are soulmates,

276
00:19:06,180 --> 00:19:07,580
but it doesn't work out.

